      <hedline>
        <hl1>Our Gift, Away From the Holiday Crowd</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas Deutsch letter on weary holiday shoppers (Dec 9 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''The Weary Holiday Shopper Is Giving Plastic This Season'' (front page, Dec. 9) did not mention shortcomings of some gift cards, like a fee for buying them online or by telephone and a deduction of a monthly fee if the card is not used up after a few months.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''The Weary Holiday Shopper Is Giving Plastic This Season'' (front page, Dec. 9) did not mention shortcomings of some gift cards, like a fee for buying them online or by telephone and a deduction of a monthly fee if the card is not used up after a few months.</p>
        <p>It is like charging you to open a savings account and then paying you negative interest.</p>
        <p>THOMAS DEUTSCH  Hartsdale, N.Y., Dec. 9, 2002</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
